Develop on local
1. cd in projects/my_site
2. open project in sublime using: `subl .`
3. start server by running `node index.js`


How to make a change and get it up on production
1. Make a change
2. run `git status` to see the changes, double check them 
3. run `git commit -m "add message here" ` - This will commit your changes with the message
4. run `git push origin head` - takes your local commit and pushes it up to github
5. run `git push heroku master` - this will take your changes on github and push htem up to heroku


